Pinus montezumae

   [8640.jpg]
   Authority Lamb.
   Family Pinopsida:Pinaceae
   Synonyms
   Common names Montezuma pine, rough-barked Mexican pine, pinheiro de
   Montezuma
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 8640

   Notes
   BRIEF DESCRIPTION
   An evergreen tree reaching a height of 25-40 m and a trunk diameter up
   to 60-100 cm.
   KILLING T
   Moterately resistant to frost.
   GROWING PERIOD
   Perennial. The tree can withstand drought periods up to 6 momths.
   COMMON NAMES
   Montezuma pine, Ocote, Boshtoj.
   FURTHER INF
   Montezuma pine can be found at elevations from 600 to 3000 m. The tree
   occur naturally within the latitudinal range of 14-23Â°N. It can adapt
   to a wide range of environments. It is shade tolerant in youth and it
   is fire resistant. Annual wood production potential is 6-12 m3/ha.

   Sources
   SOURCES
   Webb D 1984 pp 219 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, FER, DEP, KTMP, LIG,
   USE]
   INSPIRE species 136 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, FER, LIG, USE]
   Morandini R 1961 pp 130-131 [FER, TEXT]
   Serrano C 1978 pp 20-21 [RAIN, TEMP, TEXT, PH, DRA, DEP]

